  "prompt": "What is best free one page theme for WordPress?",
  "response": "Selecting the \u201cbest\u201d free one-page theme for WordPress can depend on your specific needs, such as design preference, functionality, and compatibility with plugins. However, here are some popular options that are well-regarded for their design and flexibility:\n\n1. **Sydney**: Sydney is a powerful business theme that provides a fast way for companies or freelancers to create an awesome online presence. It is highly customizable and has plenty of options for fonts, colors, and layout.\n\n2. **Hestia**: Hestia is a modern WordPress theme suitable for all types of businesses. It's highly customizable and well-suited for one-page website designs with its smooth scrolling and elegant sections.\n\n3. **Astra**: Although Astra is not strictly a one-page theme, it is highly customizable and lightweight. With Astra, you can easily create a one-page site using its drag-and-drop features and comprehensive settings.\n\n4. **Zerif Lite (also known as Zelle Lite)**: Zelle Lite is an elegant and simple to use one-page theme. It's fully responsive and offers a modern design with parallax scrolling and interactive elements.\n\n5. **One Page Express**: This theme is specifically designed for one-page layouts. It comes with a pre-designed home page, features over 30 content sections, and supports video and slideshow backgrounds.\n\n6. **Neve**: Neve is a flexible and lightweight theme that works well for one-page sites. It\u2019s SEO-optimized, fast, and integrates seamlessly with popular page builders for easy customization.\n\n7. **OceanWP**: OceanWP is a versatile theme that is lightweight and extendable. It's not limited to one-page designs, but with its many customization options, you can achieve a great one-page layout.\n\n8. **OnePress**: OnePress is an outstanding creative and flexible theme perfect for business websites, portfolio, digital agency, product showcase, freelancers, and everyone else who appreciates good design.\n\nWhen selecting a theme, consider the specific features you require, such as plugin compatibility, the ability to be customized, and performance on mobile devices. Testing a few themes to see which best meets your expectations is always a good idea.",
